video.title: Highlight: Twitch Plays (Viewers play/Chat plays) "Super Mario 64" on a real N64 console, type "!help" to learn how to play

commenter.name: yugi601
commenter.bio: (Primarily streaming on YouTube for now!)

message.body: @literally_snorlax Valid inputs are A, B, Z, L, R, Start, CUp, CDown, CLeft, CRight (C buttons), DUp, DDown, DLeft, DRight (D-Pad, unused in most games), Up, Down, Left and Right (Analog stick, used in almost every game as the standard movement input). Typos work too! Directions can be replaced with cardinal directions: N, S, W, E, North, South, West, East, this works for C buttons and D-Pad too. ex: CN, CNorth, DS, DSouth, etc. Up to 3 DIFFERENT commands can be used at the same time:

Typos work too! Directions can be replaced with cardinal directions: N, S, W, E, North, South, West, East, this works for C buttons and D-Pad too. ex: CN, CNorth, DS, DSouth, etc. Up to 3 DIFFERENT commands can be used at the same time:

message.body: b+up+right. You can't combine opposite commands: Left+Right, Up+Down, etc., WILL NOT WORK. End your input with - to hold down indefinitely until the next input comes: a+z+right-. Alternatively, you can type Wait or Stop to stop the execution of a held input. Sending a normal (Non-held) input if the input is the same as the current held input, it will just hold for a little longer before releasing. Normal (Non-held) inputs last 133 milliseconds, which is around 8 frames on a game that runs at

message.body: @LeonixGamerIII Valid inputs are A, B, Z, L, R, Start, CUp, CDown, CLeft, CRight (C buttons), DUp, DDown, DLeft, DRight (D-Pad, unused in most games), Up, Down, Left and Right (Analog stick, used in almost every game as the standard movement input). Typos work too! Directions can be replaced with cardinal directions: N, S, W, E, North, South, West, East, this works for C buttons and D-Pad too. ex: CN, CNorth, DS, DSouth, etc. Up to 3 DIFFERENT commands can be used at the same time: b+up+right.

message.body: You can't combine opposite commands: Left+Right, Up+Down, etc., WILL NOT WORK. End your input with - to hold down indefinitely until the next input comes: a+z+right-. Alternatively, you can type Wait or Stop to stop the execution of a held input. Sending a normal (Non-held) input if the input is the same as the current held input, it will just hold for a little longer before releasing. Normal (Non-held) inputs last 133 milliseconds, which is around 8 frames on a game that runs at 60fps.
